snippet: The New York City medical examiner’s report attributed the comedian’s death to brain damage that resulted from low blood oxygen.
abstract: New York City medical examiner rules that death of comedian Joan Rivers was caused by 'therapeutic complication' during routine medical procedures; does not cite medical error but does not rule out possibility of malpractice.
lead_paragraph: The New York City medical examiner’s report attributed the comedian’s death to brain damage that resulted from low blood oxygen.
